theirvoices become shaky, that is not a comment on anyone here.
Also,please don&#39;t misread what I actually said. The point I made, or
triedto make, about the investigators not hearing what I heard...
Iwouldn&#39;t have heard all of it in real time either. Too many
layers,too fast, etc. I have the luxury now of sitting and analyzing
the filein my own time. As for fear being a factor... I do believe
that the attitude of theinvestigators present during a session does
effect the outcome. EvenBruce who would rather cut my eyeballs out
with a razor has said thesame. If you think that I am scared, fine. If
I&#39;m missing one thing itis probably a healthy dose of fear. Don&#39;t make
the mistake of missingthe points by name calling. I post my thoughts
here because it is an active group of peopleworking with this form of
ITC. You can call me a shit stirrer orwhatever you want. The point is
that I see issues that could beaddressed fairly easily. You can ignore
it or deflect all you want.For me, it&#39;s not about being friends, it&#39;s
about the research. --- In EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com, Frank Ratka
